Hungarian Stocks Gain Third Day Led by OTP as Forint Advances

-- B y   A n d r a s   G e r g e l y
-- 
2011-10-12T08:40:36Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-12/hungarian-stocks-gain-third-day-led-by-otp-as-forint-advances.html
Hungarian shares rose for a third
straight day, led by gains in OTP Bank Nyrt.,  Hungary ’s largest
lender. The forint appreciated.  The benchmark BUX index of shares rallied 1.1 percent to
17,196 by 10:26 a.m. in Budapest. OTP, which has a 27 percent
weighting in the BUX, jumped 1.8 percent to 3,360 forint.
Hungary’s currency strengthened 0.5 percent to 293.6 per euro.  To contact the reporter on this story:
